div4.p:
 As soon as the meeting adjourned, the crowd proceeded to make preparations for the erection of a secession pole and flag, the latter of which was made by the fair fingers of the fairest of Hampton's daughters.

I hear that it is in contemplation to erect one on a larger scale, next Saturday, as this, gotten upon the spur of the occasion, is not commensurate with the spirit of those who had it in charge, nor of the people.

Wild hurrahs and volleys of musketry greeted it, as it flung its folds to the breeze;
